"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "pervades, his person"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "his inside:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or, accord. to some,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having any disease:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "emaciated by disease so as to be at the point of death:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mudonafN", "text_ar": "مُدْنَفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mudonifN", "text_ar": "مُدْنِفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signify the same: (M:) or these two signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rendered heavy by disease"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "so as to be near to death,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "at the point of death:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see 1]: (S, Mgh, K:) [and Freytag adds ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAnifN", "text_ar": "دَانِفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", explained as meaning “ interitui obnoxius, ” as from the Ham; in which I only find (p. 624) authority for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "danifN", "text_ar": "دَنِفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "being at the point of death"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "destruction:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "danafN", "text_ar": "دَنَفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used alike as masc. (Fr, T, S, M, K) and fem. (S, M, K) and sing. (Fr, T, S, M, K) and dual (S, M) and pl., (Fr, T, S, M, K,) as though it were an inf. n. used as an epithet: (M:) but if you say ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "danifN", "text_ar": "دَنِفٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", you vary it for the fem. and dual and pl., (T, * S, M, K,) saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AimoraA^apN danifapN", "text_ar": "اِمْرَاَةٌ دَنِفَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M,) &c., (S,) i. e., saying also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulaAni danifaAni", "text_ar": "رَجُلَانِ دَنِفَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qawomN A^adonaAfN", "text_ar": "قَوْمٌ اَدْنَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (M,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rijaAlN A^adonaAfN", "text_ar": "رِجَالٌ اَدْنَافٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) and sometimes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "danafN", "text_ar": "دَنَفٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has a dual form and a pl.; (K;) [i. e.] one may say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^axawaAka danafaAni", "text_ar": "اَخَوَاكَ دَنَفَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ixowatuka A^adonaAfu", "text_ar": "اـِخْوَتُكَ اَدْنَافُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (Fr, T.) ―         -b2-  Applied to the sun, it means (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Near to setting,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "becoming yellow."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA.) So in the saying (of El-'Ajjáj, T, TA),"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "waAl$~amosu qado kaAdato takuwnu danafaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the sun had almost become near to setting, and to turning yellow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (T, M, TA.) [See Q. 2 in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "zHlf", "text_ar": "زحلف"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "K", "Msb", "Mgh", "Fr", "T", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}